# Cape Coast Shoreline Change — Figure Gallery
*6 Publication-Quality Figures for Thesis Results & Discussion*

---

## Figure 1: Erosion vs. Accretion Rate Map
Shows the 187 transect points color-coded by their annual rate of change (m/yr). **Red = Erosion** | **Blue = Accretion**.

![Erosion vs Accretion Map](file:///C:/Users/LENOVO/.gemini/antigravity/brain/d3011edc-0e68-4460-85c5-8e57da2c2d6e/fig1_erosion_accretion_map.png)

---

## Figure 2: Temporal Shoreline Migration (2000–2023)
All 24 annual shorelines plotted together. **Dark/Purple = Older (2000)** | **Bright/Yellow = Recent (2023)**. Bold lines highlight 2000, 2010, 2020, and 2023.

![Temporal Shoreline Migration](file:///C:/Users/LENOVO/.gemini/antigravity/brain/d3011edc-0e68-4460-85c5-8e57da2c2d6e/fig2_temporal_shoreline_migration.png)

---

## Figure 3: Net Shoreline Movement (NSM) Hotspot Map
Circle size represents the magnitude of net shoreline shift between 2000 and 2023. **Red = Landward retreat (erosion)** | **Green = Seaward growth (accretion)**. Larger circles = more change.

![NSM Hotspot Map](file:///C:/Users/LENOVO/.gemini/antigravity/brain/d3011edc-0e68-4460-85c5-8e57da2c2d6e/fig3_nsm_hotspot_map.png)

---

## Figure 4: Rate of Change Distribution Histogram
The statistical distribution of all 187 shoreline change rates. The dashed yellow line shows the mean. The inset box reports summary statistics.

![Rate of Change Histogram](file:///C:/Users/LENOVO/.gemini/antigravity/brain/d3011edc-0e68-4460-85c5-8e57da2c2d6e/fig4_rate_histogram.png)

---

## Figure 5: Decadal Shoreline Position Comparison
The mean distance of the shoreline from baseline at four key epochs. Error bars represent the standard deviation across all 187 transects.

![Decadal Comparison](file:///C:/Users/LENOVO/.gemini/antigravity/brain/d3011edc-0e68-4460-85c5-8e57da2c2d6e/fig5_decadal_comparison.png)

---

## Figure 6: Time Series — Top 5 Most Eroding Transects
Temporal profiles of the 5 transects experiencing the most severe erosion. Each line tracks how a single transect's shoreline position has shifted year-by-year from 2000 to 2023.

![Time Series Top Eroding](file:///C:/Users/LENOVO/.gemini/antigravity/brain/d3011edc-0e68-4460-85c5-8e57da2c2d6e/fig6_timeseries_top_eroding.png)

